The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for object segmentation in images, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed architecture is based on recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of structured prediction, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
